						               													<description>On Aderstrom the world has turned to darkness. Powerful beings have learned to tap into the planet&amp;rsquo;s core, the only true energy source.  The once peaceful Aderstrom has become a world full of darkness torn apart by the violent struggle for dominance. Amid this darkness one beacon of hope has arisen. Thea, using the same power of the world&amp;rsquo;s core, fights to redeem her world from the chaos that now prevails.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Massive Core, players use a leader deck representing a faction from Aderstrom.  The players create a &amp;ldquo;board&amp;rdquo; using locations cards and leader cards to create a 5 x 5 grid.  They then battle each other by playing characters, some revealed and some unrevealed, and blasts to do damage to their opponent&amp;rsquo;s forces and CoreTap.  If a player can do 24 damage to the opponent&amp;rsquo;s CoreTap, that player wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Massive Core is a free print and play game released with a Creative Commons license (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0).  The game will be crowd-developed with quarterly releases of official content. Players interested in contributing to the game&amp;rsquo;s development can join the Massive Core forum and propose rule changes, cards, factions, add possible art for cards, design 3D components, or come up with story ideas.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
